1
00:00:09,297 --> 00:00:11,032
Your new condo is freaking luxurious.

2
00:00:11,351 --> 00:00:12,482
I got a discount.

3
00:00:12,693 --> 00:00:14,511
- How much?
- 70%.

4
00:00:14,539 --> 00:00:17,330
Do you know that where you’re sleeping is right on top of where I died?

5
00:00:17,484 --> 00:00:18,891
I can do anything to you.

6
00:00:19,127 --> 00:00:20,456
Open the door for me.

7
00:00:20,573 --> 00:00:23,561
If you don’t, I’ll puke right in front of your room.

8
00:00:25,167 --> 00:00:26,336
Time to wake up.

9
00:00:28,005 --> 00:00:28,894
I’m serious.

10
00:00:29,022 --> 00:00:31,042
I feel like Meen didn’t kill me.

11
00:00:31,442 --> 00:00:32,650
If it wasn’t me, then who was it?

12
00:00:32,868 --> 00:00:34,920
Who else do you think saw what happened besides...?

13
00:00:36,468 --> 00:00:37,847
Can you help me talk to the ghost in the room?

14
00:00:38,158 --> 00:00:38,994
No.

15
00:00:39,554 --> 00:00:40,448
Hey, wait.

16
00:00:48,050 --> 00:00:48,950
Hey.

17
00:00:51,640 --> 00:00:54,050
I heard you locked P'Arthit in the bathroom.

18
00:00:54,570 --> 00:00:56,530
And you even shut the door in his face?

19
00:00:57,000 --> 00:00:57,960
Shit.

20
00:01:08,280 --> 00:01:09,030
Help me out, will you?

21
00:01:09,370 --> 00:01:10,600
- Help me talk to the ghost in the room.
- No.

22
00:01:10,950 --> 00:01:11,500
Hey, wait.

23
00:01:28,540 --> 00:01:29,210
North.

24
00:01:30,620 --> 00:01:33,670
Your friend is so unbelievable.

25
00:03:07,180 --> 00:03:08,070
Yeah.

26
00:03:08,640 --> 00:03:10,630
Last night he made me sleep in the bathroom.

27
00:03:11,370 --> 00:03:13,340
Damn it, I haven’t even settled the score with him yet.

28
00:03:13,730 --> 00:03:14,870
And today he did it again.

29
00:03:15,350 --> 00:03:16,690
He shut the door in my face.

30
00:03:17,610 --> 00:03:19,620
He really left you sleeping in the bathroom?

31
00:03:20,270 --> 00:03:21,220
That’s bold.

32
00:03:21,610 --> 00:03:22,770
That’s my friend.

33
00:03:24,730 --> 00:03:26,980
You think that’s funny?

34
00:03:28,420 --> 00:03:29,700
So what do you want from him?

35
00:03:34,980 --> 00:03:37,460
I just want him to help me with something.

36
00:03:40,610 --> 00:03:43,060
Why don’t you at least hear him out about what he’s asking?

37
00:03:43,610 --> 00:03:49,120
It seems like his friend wasn’t killed by her boyfriend after all.

38
00:03:49,480 --> 00:03:51,840
If she didn’t do it but still has to go to prison,

39
00:03:52,550 --> 00:03:53,890
that’s pretty pitiful.

40
00:04:07,550 --> 00:04:09,670
Why do you think your girlfriend didn’t kill you?

41
00:04:19,570 --> 00:04:21,470
Why do you think your girlfriend didn’t do it?

42
00:04:28,960 --> 00:04:31,840
Even though she had a motive.

43
00:04:32,450 --> 00:04:33,470
A motive?

44
00:04:36,790 --> 00:04:38,840
We had a big fight before that, but...

45
00:04:40,580 --> 00:04:41,930
it was a misunderstanding.

46
00:04:43,380 --> 00:04:44,470
What were you fighting about?

47
00:04:47,640 --> 00:04:49,050
She thought I was cheating on her.

48
00:04:52,330 --> 00:04:54,030
It really was a misunderstanding.

49
00:04:54,610 --> 00:04:56,170
I never cheated on her.

50
00:04:59,620 --> 00:05:01,730
Then why do you think P'Meen didn’t do it?

51
00:05:04,670 --> 00:05:07,230
Even though Meen can be hot-tempered,

52
00:05:07,730 --> 00:05:08,850
and kind of mean,

53
00:05:11,150 --> 00:05:14,870
sharp-tongued. We fought almost every day when she was in a bad mood.

54
00:05:16,090 --> 00:05:19,580
Lately, we argued because she misunderstood and thought I was cheating.

55
00:05:20,120 --> 00:05:21,490
And that night, she was drunk.

56
00:05:25,390 --> 00:05:26,850
But she wouldn’t kill me, right?

57
00:05:30,690 --> 00:05:31,840
I don’t know.

58
00:05:33,180 --> 00:05:34,960
You don’t remember anything from that night?

59
00:05:36,060 --> 00:05:37,140
Not at all.

60
00:05:38,340 --> 00:05:40,650
By the time I realized I was dead, several days had passed.

61
00:05:41,250 --> 00:05:43,660
Why don’t you try asking the other ghosts in the room?

62
00:05:49,550 --> 00:05:51,220
Do you think I haven’t tried?

63
00:06:03,240 --> 00:06:04,720
P'Praw.

64
00:06:10,020 --> 00:06:13,170
About that night...

65
00:06:33,250 --> 00:06:35,240
When I was killed,

66
00:06:36,230 --> 00:06:38,670
did you see anything, P'Earng?

67
00:06:45,786 --> 00:06:46,990
P'Cream.

68
00:06:47,290 --> 00:06:49,360
You’re my last hope.

69
00:06:56,610 --> 00:06:57,470
Dao.

70
00:06:58,950 --> 00:06:59,920
Be careful.

71
00:07:00,400 --> 00:07:02,620
P'Cream is the scariest one.

72
00:07:06,230 --> 00:07:07,110
Dao.

73
00:07:09,320 --> 00:07:10,780
Dao.

74
00:07:22,950 --> 00:07:24,000
Aren’t you scared?

75
00:07:25,360 --> 00:07:26,030
No.

76
00:07:26,650 --> 00:07:28,060
Do you want to stay with me?

77
00:07:30,540 --> 00:07:31,280
No.

78
00:07:33,290 --> 00:07:34,490
Why?

79
00:07:37,290 --> 00:07:39,450
Why don’t you want to stay with me?

80
00:07:41,760 --> 00:07:43,760
Why did you kill me?

81
00:07:44,070 --> 00:07:46,220
Why did you have someone else?

82
00:07:48,970 --> 00:07:52,420
This isn’t a concert. Why are you screaming?

83
00:07:58,010 --> 00:07:59,340
I want to go.

84
00:07:59,880 --> 00:08:00,520
Huh?

85
00:08:01,820 --> 00:08:03,140
I want to go to a concert.

86
00:08:10,730 --> 00:08:12,360
You like going to concerts?

87
00:08:16,010 --> 00:08:17,210
I like them too.

88
00:08:18,970 --> 00:08:20,230
Are you a fan too?

89
00:08:21,870 --> 00:08:23,390
Not that hardcore.

90
00:08:24,020 --> 00:08:25,690
But I follow quite a few bands.

91
00:08:26,700 --> 00:08:29,250
I’m a pro at getting concert tickets.

92
00:08:45,250 --> 00:08:46,560
Dao’s pretty impressive.

93
00:08:47,890 --> 00:08:49,420
You even managed to calm P'Cream down.

94
00:08:50,840 --> 00:08:52,270
She’s the scariest one here.

95
00:08:58,420 --> 00:09:01,080
Everyone has their exceptions.

96
00:09:04,960 --> 00:09:06,570
Um, P'Cream.

97
00:09:07,070 --> 00:09:07,740
Hmm?

98
00:09:09,490 --> 00:09:11,540
The night P'Donut was killed,

99
00:09:12,610 --> 00:09:14,270
did you see anything, P'Cream?

100
00:09:15,800 --> 00:09:17,050
I didn’t see anything.

101
00:09:17,980 --> 00:09:19,300
I was in the bathroom.

102
00:09:19,840 --> 00:09:20,950
But the sound of arguing

103
00:09:21,010 --> 00:09:22,240
was really loud.

104
00:09:24,770 --> 00:09:27,130
Was it P'Donut and P'Meen arguing?

105
00:09:28,880 --> 00:09:29,960
No.

106
00:09:30,350 --> 00:09:31,810
It was Donut and someone else.

107
00:09:38,000 --> 00:09:39,150
Whose voice was it?

108
00:09:41,330 --> 00:09:42,490
I don’t know.

109
00:09:43,030 --> 00:09:44,060
It didn’t sound familiar at all.

110
00:09:46,510 --> 00:09:48,930
Was it a woman or a man?

111
00:09:53,110 --> 00:09:53,990
A woman.

112
00:10:18,850 --> 00:10:21,140
Alright, alright. I get it.

113
00:10:21,390 --> 00:10:23,060
Are you trying to knock the door down or what—

114
00:10:30,110 --> 00:10:31,730
P'Cream said

115
00:10:32,950 --> 00:10:35,090
that on the night P'Donut was killed,

116
00:10:35,790 --> 00:10:38,800
she heard him arguing with another woman,

117
00:10:40,120 --> 00:10:41,310
not P'Meen.

118
00:10:43,070 --> 00:10:44,550
That’s all she said.

119
00:10:44,920 --> 00:10:46,400
I haven’t seen the others yet,

120
00:10:47,350 --> 00:10:48,620
so I haven’t asked them.

121
00:10:49,350 --> 00:10:50,590
Wait.

122
00:10:57,240 --> 00:10:58,570
So you’re going to help me, right?

123
00:11:03,010 --> 00:11:06,050
I’m helping P'Donut, not you.

124
00:11:12,620 --> 00:11:14,330
Isn’t that basically the same thing?

125
00:11:14,440 --> 00:11:15,140
No, it’s not.

126
00:11:31,480 --> 00:11:33,470
Damn, he's actually a good person.

127
00:11:35,630 --> 00:11:38,120
Yeah. Unlike you, Thit.

128
00:11:42,350 --> 00:11:43,780
You little—

129
00:11:43,950 --> 00:11:44,510
jerk.

130
00:11:45,630 --> 00:11:48,090
- Damn it.
- I’m just kidding.

131
00:11:48,790 --> 00:11:50,120
Stop floating around like that, you creep.

132
00:12:06,870 --> 00:12:08,470
Or maybe he was arguing with another woman.

133
00:12:11,520 --> 00:12:14,020
But there aren’t any other women around Do.

134
00:12:14,130 --> 00:12:14,930
True.

135
00:12:16,440 --> 00:12:18,310
I only have Meen. I love only Meen.

136
00:12:19,860 --> 00:12:20,830
Shit.

137
00:12:21,960 --> 00:12:23,690
Or did he actually have a side chick?

138
00:12:24,180 --> 00:12:26,640
Watch your mouth.

139
00:12:29,590 --> 00:12:32,580
I doubt it. Do’s way too shy.

140
00:12:37,840 --> 00:12:39,230
Or maybe it was someone around Meen.

141
00:12:40,580 --> 00:12:42,610
Yeah, I think so too.

142
00:12:53,360 --> 00:12:55,030
I can’t even read this properly.

143
00:12:55,080 --> 00:12:56,900
Just keep reading.

144
00:12:56,930 --> 00:12:58,500
So pretty. That lipstick color is gorgeous.

145
00:12:59,830 --> 00:13:01,780
So, are you going tonight, Meen?

146
00:13:03,750 --> 00:13:05,140
I think I’ll pass.

147
00:13:05,810 --> 00:13:08,140
Do will bring me to a buffet.

148
00:13:09,020 --> 00:13:10,750
Fine, go be with your husband.

149
00:13:11,500 --> 00:13:13,040
O-lin isn’t going either.

150
00:13:13,760 --> 00:13:16,450
I don’t drink, so it wouldn’t be fun for me.

151
00:13:17,020 --> 00:13:18,120
Drink for me, then.

152
00:13:18,870 --> 00:13:20,240
Guess I’ll just go alone.

153
00:13:20,860 --> 00:13:22,000
I’d rather read a book.

154
00:13:23,760 --> 00:13:26,310
I seriously don’t get you, Meen.

155
00:13:26,870 --> 00:13:29,870
So many guys are into you, and you chose that bland guy.

156
00:13:32,800 --> 00:13:34,270
I'm delusional, I guess.

157
00:13:34,980 --> 00:13:35,720
I’m heading out.

158
00:13:36,510 --> 00:13:38,230
- Bye.
- Bye.

159
00:13:38,670 --> 00:13:39,340
See you.

160
00:13:40,520 --> 00:13:41,330
That’s how it is once you’ve got a man.

161
00:13:50,314 --> 00:13:53,540
You should just break up. I see you two arguing every day.

162
00:13:55,340 --> 00:13:56,610
But I love him.

163
00:13:58,657 --> 00:14:02,160
I know you do. If you argue over trivial things, that’s one thing.

164
00:14:02,669 --> 00:14:05,000
But cheating? I can’t accept that.

165
00:14:05,174 --> 00:14:07,770
You weren’t raised to be betrayed like this, Meen.

166
00:14:09,850 --> 00:14:11,680
I’ve been with him for four or five years.

167
00:14:12,110 --> 00:14:13,960
How can I just break up that easily, Mind?

168
00:14:15,950 --> 00:14:19,232
That’s not love. You’re just attached.

169
00:14:21,450 --> 00:14:24,170
So many guys are into you, yet you picked that bland guy.

170
00:14:24,830 --> 00:14:27,100
It’s not love. You’re just attached.

171
00:14:27,130 --> 00:14:28,650
How can I break up that easily, Mind?

172
00:14:56,080 --> 00:14:56,770
Hey.

173
00:14:57,430 --> 00:14:58,390
Any updates?

174
00:14:59,070 --> 00:15:00,830
I haven’t seen P'Praw or P'Earng yet.

175
00:15:02,240 --> 00:15:03,430
Didn’t you ask Do?

176
00:15:04,160 --> 00:15:06,430
P'Do doesn’t remember anything from that night.

177
00:15:06,720 --> 00:15:08,870
And his memories from before that

178
00:15:09,300 --> 00:15:10,380
are blurry too.

179
00:15:10,810 --> 00:15:12,310
Damn it.

180
00:15:14,440 --> 00:15:16,560
How can he not even remember his own case?

181
00:15:19,670 --> 00:15:21,470
But last night, P'Do didn’t go back to his room.

182
00:15:22,930 --> 00:15:24,080
So where could he have gone?

183
00:15:25,050 --> 00:15:26,950
As for the women around them,

184
00:15:27,770 --> 00:15:29,550
there are probably just Meen’s friends,

185
00:15:29,790 --> 00:15:30,790
Meen’s sister,

186
00:15:31,710 --> 00:15:32,610
Meen’s mom,

187
00:15:33,810 --> 00:15:34,800
and Do’s mom.

188
00:15:37,720 --> 00:15:38,400
Ok.

189
00:15:38,490 --> 00:15:40,140
Alright, I’ve gotta go. I have class.

190
00:15:46,220 --> 00:15:47,810
Meen thinks she killed him.

191
00:15:48,210 --> 00:15:49,410
She woke up next to the body

192
00:15:49,720 --> 00:15:50,740
with a knife in her hand,

193
00:15:50,940 --> 00:15:52,150
so she confessed to the police.

194
00:15:54,370 --> 00:15:58,070
So right now, you suspect her friends and her older sister?

195
00:15:58,710 --> 00:15:59,260
Yeah.

196
00:16:00,220 --> 00:16:02,230
I’ve ruled out the other possibilities.

197
00:16:02,690 --> 00:16:03,550
That’s all that’s left.

198
00:16:07,800 --> 00:16:08,470
Wait a second.

199
00:16:10,950 --> 00:16:14,610
You told me the condo’s security cameras were broken that day, right?

200
00:16:14,960 --> 00:16:16,770
Yeah, the condo was under renovation at the time.

201
00:16:18,490 --> 00:16:22,340
Have you checked any other security cameras yet?

202
00:16:23,020 --> 00:16:24,620
Around the condo,

203
00:16:25,150 --> 00:16:26,140
or on the nearby streets?

204
00:16:27,430 --> 00:16:28,380
Oh shit, you’re right.

205
00:16:29,520 --> 00:16:32,150
Damn, Fah, you’re a genius.

206
00:16:32,760 --> 00:16:34,270
I’m off. Clean this up for me.

207
00:16:38,000 --> 00:16:38,760
See you.

208
00:16:43,090 --> 00:16:45,470
This is CCTV footage from the building across the street.

209
00:16:46,280 --> 00:16:47,220
I asked for it.

210
00:16:47,900 --> 00:16:49,310
Not sure if it’ll help, though.

211
00:17:02,470 --> 00:17:03,530
Yeah, that’s it.

212
00:17:03,690 --> 00:17:05,460
Damn, that was slick.

213
00:17:06,090 --> 00:17:08,440
We should totally form an e-sports team, Daotok.

214
00:17:08,530 --> 00:17:10,870
It’s rare to find someone as good as you.

215
00:17:16,050 --> 00:17:16,950
Michael.

216
00:17:17,660 --> 00:17:18,470
What?

217
00:17:19,260 --> 00:17:20,600
P'Praw is here.

218
00:17:24,550 --> 00:17:25,440
Okay.

219
00:17:26,170 --> 00:17:27,420
Hey, who are you talking to?

220
00:17:29,430 --> 00:17:31,550
P'Praw is about to jump. Hurry and talk to her, Michael.

221
00:17:31,770 --> 00:17:32,830
I know.

222
00:17:33,900 --> 00:17:35,640
Damn it, who are you talking to?

223
00:17:37,670 --> 00:17:39,440
Let’s stop here for today, North.

224
00:17:39,930 --> 00:17:41,970
I need to talk to someone.

225
00:17:42,890 --> 00:17:43,620
Who?

226
00:17:46,760 --> 00:17:47,870
The ghost in the room.

227
00:18:00,590 --> 00:18:01,240
Excuse me.

228
00:18:03,280 --> 00:18:04,560
Can I ask you something?

229
00:18:07,120 --> 00:18:08,870
On the night P'Donut was killed,

230
00:18:09,430 --> 00:18:11,580
did you see anyone in that room?

231
00:18:19,740 --> 00:18:21,790
Did you see anyone in P'Donut’s room?

232
00:18:27,570 --> 00:18:29,820
Was that person the one who killed P'Donut?

233
00:18:38,170 --> 00:18:39,020
Who was it?

234
00:18:53,020 --> 00:18:56,360
P'Praw said someone else walked into the room that night.

235
00:18:57,130 --> 00:18:59,380
Do you know who it was?

236
00:19:03,960 --> 00:19:05,230
I don’t know her.

237
00:19:06,110 --> 00:19:08,910
Do you remember what she looked like?

238
00:19:10,800 --> 00:19:11,470
A woman.

239
00:19:12,550 --> 00:19:14,020
Long hair.

240
00:19:14,760 --> 00:19:15,780
A black shirt.

241
00:19:18,140 --> 00:19:19,100
A woman.

242
00:19:19,900 --> 00:19:21,160
Long hair.

243
00:19:22,190 --> 00:19:23,180
A black shirt.

244
00:19:28,510 --> 00:19:29,790
I didn’t understand a thing in class just now.

245
00:19:31,470 --> 00:19:32,230
I even dozed off.

246
00:19:32,710 --> 00:19:33,970
You fell asleep in class?

247
00:19:35,990 --> 00:19:36,850
That’s bad.

248
00:19:42,430 --> 00:19:43,270
Thank you.

249
00:19:43,430 --> 00:19:44,060
You’re welcome.

250
00:19:54,010 --> 00:19:54,820
She feels...

251
00:19:55,680 --> 00:19:56,410
irritated.

252
00:20:03,000 --> 00:20:03,740
She feels...

253
00:20:04,220 --> 00:20:05,330
fed up.

254
00:20:22,280 --> 00:20:23,060
She feels...

255
00:20:24,370 --> 00:20:25,990
sad,

256
00:20:26,920 --> 00:20:27,890
hurt,

257
00:20:28,890 --> 00:20:30,030
afraid,

258
00:20:30,340 --> 00:20:31,370
anxious,

259
00:20:31,780 --> 00:20:32,860
and confused.

260
00:20:34,150 --> 00:20:35,010
Guilty.

261
00:20:35,180 --> 00:20:36,060
Hello?

262
00:20:37,670 --> 00:20:38,340
Hello?

263
00:20:40,190 --> 00:20:41,410
Are you okay?

264
00:20:43,650 --> 00:20:44,680
I’m fine.

265
00:20:46,090 --> 00:20:47,030
Thank you.

266
00:21:01,740 --> 00:21:03,050
What happened to your face?

267
00:21:03,630 --> 00:21:05,210
You look like a dog that got stung by bees.

268
00:21:06,320 --> 00:21:07,010
Yeah.

269
00:21:07,400 --> 00:21:08,210
Just a bit.

270
00:21:09,450 --> 00:21:10,550
What do you mean “just a bit”?

271
00:21:12,880 --> 00:21:15,390
Last night, a gang leader in prison picked a fight with me.

272
00:21:15,870 --> 00:21:16,520
Damn.

273
00:21:17,190 --> 00:21:17,790
Whatever.

274
00:21:19,400 --> 00:21:20,740
So why are you here?

275
00:21:21,280 --> 00:21:22,590
Any progress?

276
00:21:22,950 --> 00:21:25,820
- Detective Conan.
- Detective your ass.

277
00:21:26,950 --> 00:21:27,720
Idiot.

278
00:21:28,370 --> 00:21:30,490
I had him talk to the ghost in the room.

279
00:21:30,600 --> 00:21:32,000
He said you didn’t kill him.

280
00:21:32,280 --> 00:21:33,780
See? Damn it.

281
00:21:34,600 --> 00:21:36,280
He said on the night it happened,

282
00:21:37,490 --> 00:21:39,040
a woman went into your room

283
00:21:40,110 --> 00:21:41,350
and argued with Do.

284
00:21:43,130 --> 00:21:44,250
Who the hell was that?

285
00:21:44,580 --> 00:21:47,140
She killed my husband and got me thrown in jail.

286
00:21:47,530 --> 00:21:48,920
I’m so damn pissed.

287
00:21:50,590 --> 00:21:51,690
Hey, do you remember?

288
00:21:52,480 --> 00:21:55,760
Back then, the condo’s security cameras were broken, right?

289
00:21:56,320 --> 00:21:57,690
So I asked P'Pae

290
00:21:57,730 --> 00:22:00,000
to get CCTV footage from nearby buildings.

291
00:22:03,270 --> 00:22:04,300
Smart as hell.

292
00:22:07,110 --> 00:22:08,170
I got the idea from Fah.

293
00:22:08,200 --> 00:22:09,860
- You idiot.
- Hey, asshole.

294
00:22:09,920 --> 00:22:13,480
I just called you smart.
And you should told Fah to come visit me instead.

295
00:22:13,500 --> 00:22:16,800
As for you, get out of my sight.

296
00:22:16,860 --> 00:22:18,830
Fine, I’m leaving. I’m not helping you anymore.

297
00:22:18,870 --> 00:22:19,740
Hey, hey.

298
00:22:20,440 --> 00:22:21,280
I’m kidding.

299
00:22:22,900 --> 00:22:24,280
On the night it happened,

300
00:22:25,060 --> 00:22:27,000
the CCTV actually caught something.

301
00:22:28,200 --> 00:22:29,310
that someone dropped you off.

302
00:22:39,290 --> 00:22:40,450
Could it really be her?

303
00:22:41,620 --> 00:22:43,170
O-lin is quiet as hell.

304
00:22:45,170 --> 00:22:49,490
The CCTV even caught her walking out of the condo.

305
00:22:51,310 --> 00:22:53,160
Exactly at the same time Do died.

306
00:22:58,920 --> 00:23:00,000
Can you give it to the police?

307
00:23:01,210 --> 00:23:01,720
Yeah.

308
00:23:02,630 --> 00:23:05,100
I think it could be used as evidence.

309
00:23:06,150 --> 00:23:07,840
I’ll handle the rest. Don’t worry.

310
00:23:08,540 --> 00:23:09,750
- Thanks.
- Mm.

311
00:23:12,360 --> 00:23:13,080
And...

312
00:23:14,950 --> 00:23:16,950
You seriously don’t remember a damn thing about that night?

313
00:23:19,580 --> 00:23:20,510
No.

314
00:23:21,170 --> 00:23:23,850
My memory’s gone since I was at the bar.

315
00:23:25,820 --> 00:23:29,410
See? That’s what you get for going drinking without inviting me.

316
00:23:29,970 --> 00:23:30,620
Idiot.

317
00:23:30,690 --> 00:23:31,440
Yeah.

318
00:23:32,520 --> 00:23:34,940
When I get out, I’ll buy you drinks for three months.

319
00:23:34,980 --> 00:23:36,190
You said it.

320
00:23:36,260 --> 00:23:39,200
The moment it’s about alcohol, your ears perk right up.

321
00:23:44,510 --> 00:23:45,010
Hey.

322
00:23:45,720 --> 00:23:46,240
So...

323
00:23:47,620 --> 00:23:48,610
What are you going to do next?

324
00:23:49,020 --> 00:23:49,910
If you get out, I mean.

325
00:23:52,150 --> 00:23:53,110
It won’t be easy, right?

326
00:23:54,840 --> 00:23:56,070
You were with Do for so long.

327
00:24:04,560 --> 00:24:05,340
I don’t know.

328
00:24:06,650 --> 00:24:08,250
Isn’t it like in novels—

329
00:24:08,370 --> 00:24:09,000
where—

330
00:24:10,710 --> 00:24:12,420
the truth is he's not dead?

331
00:24:13,870 --> 00:24:14,660
Or like—

332
00:24:15,870 --> 00:24:17,870
- he’s in a coma and wakes up...
- That’s enough, Meen.

333
00:24:18,040 --> 00:24:22,000
I stood there and watched him being cremated with my own eyes.

334
00:24:23,060 --> 00:24:24,810
I saw his face before they cremated him.

335
00:24:32,460 --> 00:24:33,690
His funeral—

336
00:24:34,550 --> 00:24:36,160
I didn’t even get to go.

337
00:24:39,510 --> 00:24:40,730
We were together for so long.

338
00:24:43,080 --> 00:24:45,040
I didn’t even get to see him one last time.

339
00:24:53,510 --> 00:24:54,810
You know—

340
00:24:58,100 --> 00:25:01,880
nothing’s sadder than the person you love dying.

341
00:25:13,620 --> 00:25:14,360
Yeah.

342
00:25:15,700 --> 00:25:16,380
That’s how it is.

343
00:25:18,080 --> 00:25:18,890
I just—

344
00:25:19,980 --> 00:25:21,930
I can’t picture myself with anyone else.

345
00:25:24,370 --> 00:25:25,530
When I was with him,

346
00:25:26,590 --> 00:25:29,390
I even daydreamed about our wedding, like a kid.

347
00:25:31,070 --> 00:25:31,530
Like—

348
00:25:32,250 --> 00:25:34,020
wearing a wedding dress,

349
00:25:37,580 --> 00:25:38,930
having kids with him and all that.

350
00:25:48,320 --> 00:25:49,420
Why are you bringing this up?

351
00:25:51,210 --> 00:25:52,410
I’m about to cry.

352
00:25:56,880 --> 00:25:57,820
Then cry.

353
00:25:59,830 --> 00:26:00,600
It’s not weak.

354
00:26:29,870 --> 00:26:31,040
You bastard, Do.

355
00:26:32,010 --> 00:26:33,590
Kwai ngaen. (You idiot.)

356
00:26:35,450 --> 00:26:37,180
Why the hell did you leave me?

357
00:26:39,910 --> 00:26:43,170
It’d be better if you left me for someone else than left me by dying.

358
00:26:45,050 --> 00:26:46,720
You're even flirt with me first.

359
00:26:49,280 --> 00:26:51,320
How am I supposed to live?

360
00:26:53,200 --> 00:26:55,480
How am I supposed to live?

361
00:27:02,620 --> 00:27:03,370
Uh—

362
00:27:04,700 --> 00:27:05,360
Meen.

363
00:27:10,880 --> 00:27:12,080
What the hell is a “kwai ngaen”?

364
00:27:35,140 --> 00:27:39,080
There’s nothing sadder than the person you love dying, damn it.

365
00:28:03,510 --> 00:28:05,850
Damn it, I’m trying to sleep here.

366
00:28:06,980 --> 00:28:07,730
What is it?

367
00:28:08,560 --> 00:28:09,450
I can’t sleep.

368
00:28:10,450 --> 00:28:12,700
Do I look like a sleeping pill to you? Huh?

369
00:28:12,910 --> 00:28:15,720
You can’t sleep so you call me whining like a kid.

370
00:28:16,280 --> 00:28:17,620
You’re a grown-ass adult.

371
00:28:21,070 --> 00:28:22,060
I miss you, Direk.

372
00:28:26,020 --> 00:28:27,380
What happened?

373
00:28:29,140 --> 00:28:31,220
Do you remember Do, the one who was murdered?

374
00:28:32,460 --> 00:28:33,140
Yeah.

375
00:28:34,220 --> 00:28:34,940
He’s...

376
00:28:38,400 --> 00:28:39,550
He’s already dead.

377
00:28:41,630 --> 00:28:43,600
But he’s still lingering in the room, Direk.

378
00:28:52,690 --> 00:28:53,780
Do you think—

379
00:29:00,090 --> 00:29:01,560
my mom might still be around?

380
00:29:08,590 --> 00:29:10,200
Your mom… she’s not here anymore.

381
00:29:11,410 --> 00:29:13,550
Emma’s gone.

382
00:29:29,080 --> 00:29:29,950
Michael.

383
00:29:35,040 --> 00:29:36,400
Where did you go, P'Do?

384
00:29:38,320 --> 00:29:39,640
I went to clear my head.

385
00:29:42,880 --> 00:29:43,800
I remember now.

386
00:29:46,620 --> 00:29:47,920
What happened that night.

387
00:30:07,180 --> 00:30:08,260
Babe.

388
00:30:09,830 --> 00:30:11,220
You’re back?

389
00:30:12,630 --> 00:30:14,110
You’re back?

390
00:30:18,250 --> 00:30:20,430
I didn’t cheat on you, Meen.

391
00:30:22,020 --> 00:30:24,050
There’s only you.

392
00:30:30,750 --> 00:30:32,190
What does she have that I don’t?

393
00:30:33,200 --> 00:30:34,770
Why can’t you like me?

394
00:30:42,100 --> 00:30:43,010
Meen.

395
00:30:46,670 --> 00:30:48,030
I love you, Meen.

396
00:30:53,740 --> 00:30:55,240
I really do like you.

397
00:30:57,470 --> 00:30:58,900
I’ve liked you for a long time.

398
00:31:02,620 --> 00:31:03,420
Lin.

399
00:31:06,600 --> 00:31:07,970
I told you already,

400
00:31:08,560 --> 00:31:10,180
I don’t like you.

401
00:31:10,680 --> 00:31:12,600
And I’ll never like you either.

402
00:31:13,580 --> 00:31:14,520
Lin.

403
00:31:15,420 --> 00:31:17,100
You’re Meen’s friend.

404
00:31:17,450 --> 00:31:18,800
Why are you doing this?

405
00:31:21,250 --> 00:31:21,960
Hey, Lin.

406
00:31:22,770 --> 00:31:23,430
Lin.

407
00:31:23,760 --> 00:31:25,200
Calm down. What are you doing?

408
00:31:25,470 --> 00:31:26,460
Put the knife down, Lin.

409
00:31:26,820 --> 00:31:27,310
No.

410
00:31:28,150 --> 00:31:31,120
I’ll put it down only if you accept my feeling.

411
00:31:32,260 --> 00:31:32,900
Lin.

412
00:31:33,990 --> 00:31:35,120
Nothing’s going to change.

413
00:31:35,190 --> 00:31:36,000
Don’t come any closer.

414
00:31:36,460 --> 00:31:37,100
Lin.

415
00:31:38,220 --> 00:31:39,490
Lin, calm down.

416
00:31:45,390 --> 00:31:46,600
- Lin.
- Let go.

417
00:31:46,910 --> 00:31:48,150
- Do.
- Lin.

418
00:31:48,210 --> 00:31:49,710
Let go.

419
00:32:27,780 --> 00:32:29,050
I thought Arthit came to visit.

420
00:32:30,720 --> 00:32:31,410
Who’s this?

421
00:32:34,600 --> 00:32:35,580
My name’s Daotok.

422
00:32:37,630 --> 00:32:39,580
I’m the one living in your old room.

423
00:32:41,660 --> 00:32:43,090
The one next to Arthit’s room?

424
00:32:43,860 --> 00:32:45,220
The kid who can see ghosts?

425
00:32:46,240 --> 00:32:46,890
Yes.

426
00:32:49,960 --> 00:32:50,610
So—

427
00:32:52,370 --> 00:32:53,540
why did you come see me?

428
00:32:55,990 --> 00:32:58,220
I think I know who the killer is.

429
00:32:58,570 --> 00:32:59,010
Hey—

430
00:33:00,670 --> 00:33:01,260
Wait.

431
00:33:02,970 --> 00:33:04,000
Let me brace myself first.

432
00:33:12,480 --> 00:33:12,910
Who?

433
00:33:17,390 --> 00:33:18,330
P'O-lin.

434
00:33:21,470 --> 00:33:22,390
Your friend.

435
00:33:32,090 --> 00:33:33,170
Are you sure?

436
00:33:37,900 --> 00:33:39,950
It might sound a bit unbelievable,

437
00:33:41,590 --> 00:33:43,920
but I can read people’s feelings.

438
00:33:46,860 --> 00:33:48,300
When I met P'O-lin,

439
00:33:49,130 --> 00:33:51,210
her heart was filled with guilt,

440
00:33:51,730 --> 00:33:52,920
sorrow,

441
00:33:53,770 --> 00:33:55,200
self-disappointment,

442
00:33:56,460 --> 00:33:57,640
and fear.

443
00:34:03,430 --> 00:34:05,650
You’re not here to ask me to forgive her, right?

444
00:34:07,360 --> 00:34:08,210
No.

445
00:34:10,800 --> 00:34:13,220
I believe P'O-lin will turn herself in.

446
00:34:14,240 --> 00:34:16,380
Because her feelings

447
00:34:17,350 --> 00:34:20,220
are too heavy for one person to bear.

448
00:34:23,230 --> 00:34:24,950
She just needs a little push,

449
00:34:26,490 --> 00:34:28,070
and it’ll all explode.

450
00:34:28,790 --> 00:34:29,570
A push?

451
00:34:31,920 --> 00:34:33,520
Why the hell did you kill my friend?

452
00:34:36,860 --> 00:34:39,660
- I’m sorry.
- Go apologize to Meen.

453
00:34:39,780 --> 00:34:41,020
She’s in prison because of you.

454
00:34:44,090 --> 00:34:46,330
I didn’t mean to.

455
00:34:46,900 --> 00:34:48,220
I didn’t mean to.

456
00:34:48,250 --> 00:34:49,640
Stop crying already.

457
00:34:58,410 --> 00:35:00,290
I’ve got evidence against you.

458
00:35:00,580 --> 00:35:02,380
Are you going to confess to the police yourself,

459
00:35:04,160 --> 00:35:06,840
or do I have to drag you there?

460
00:35:08,030 --> 00:35:10,060
I’ll turn myself in.

461
00:35:12,200 --> 00:35:13,770
I’ll go apologize to Meen.

462
00:35:15,470 --> 00:35:17,070
I truly feel guilty.

463
00:35:17,430 --> 00:35:18,830
I didn’t mean to.

464
00:35:19,460 --> 00:35:20,060
Wait—

465
00:35:20,550 --> 00:35:22,150
So his girlfriend wasn’t the killer?

466
00:35:23,190 --> 00:35:23,730
Wait—

467
00:35:24,180 --> 00:35:25,490
So she went to jail for nothing?

468
00:35:26,190 --> 00:35:27,580
That’s messed up.

469
00:35:28,530 --> 00:35:29,850
And they were best friends too, right?

470
00:35:36,190 --> 00:35:37,140
Damn it.

471
00:35:38,170 --> 00:35:40,070
Turns out the trigger was Arthit.

472
00:35:40,670 --> 00:35:41,600
That sucks for you, Lin.

473
00:35:44,450 --> 00:35:44,950
And—

474
00:35:47,950 --> 00:35:49,140
how’s Do?

475
00:35:51,400 --> 00:35:52,310
P'Do—

476
00:35:54,350 --> 00:35:55,990
he’s still waiting for you at the same place.

477
00:36:06,830 --> 00:36:07,580
Damn.

478
00:36:08,280 --> 00:36:09,910
He’s pathetic as hell.

479
00:36:10,750 --> 00:36:13,450
Without me, he can’t do shit.

480
00:36:22,190 --> 00:36:24,560
P'Donut feels really guilty

481
00:36:25,170 --> 00:36:27,170
for making you unable to trust him.

482
00:36:29,150 --> 00:36:31,580
That he truly had only you.

483
00:36:34,380 --> 00:36:36,040
Why the hell should he feel guilty?

484
00:36:38,040 --> 00:36:38,830
I’m the one

485
00:36:39,250 --> 00:36:40,160
who should feel guilty

486
00:36:40,910 --> 00:36:41,970
for not trusting him,

487
00:36:42,950 --> 00:36:44,340
for thinking he had someone else,

488
00:36:45,660 --> 00:36:47,040
when someone like him

489
00:36:47,720 --> 00:36:50,750
has absolutely nothing worth being jealous over.

490
00:36:59,700 --> 00:37:01,070
I told you already,

491
00:37:02,530 --> 00:37:04,610
I can read people’s feelings.

492
00:37:06,000 --> 00:37:07,970
So if you’re sad,

493
00:37:10,610 --> 00:37:12,170
please let yourself cry.

494
00:37:52,200 --> 00:37:53,620
Welcome back, buddy.

495
00:37:54,680 --> 00:37:55,480
My dear friend.

496
00:37:55,790 --> 00:37:56,310
Damn.

497
00:37:56,670 --> 00:37:58,410
You’re that happy I’m out?

498
00:37:58,790 --> 00:37:59,770
Of course I am.

499
00:37:59,960 --> 00:38:02,300
I get free drinks for three months.

500
00:38:03,040 --> 00:38:05,070
Damn, all you think about is booze.

501
00:38:05,210 --> 00:38:07,530
If it weren’t for you getting me out of jail,

502
00:38:08,220 --> 00:38:10,120
- I’d pinch your balls black and blue.
- You asshole, Meen. Damn it.

503
00:38:10,800 --> 00:38:13,110
That tickles, man.
I jumped. I’m serious.

504
00:38:13,400 --> 00:38:16,940
- Hey, I’m serious too. Come here, let me grab them.
- Don’t, you bastard. No way.

505
00:38:18,160 --> 00:38:19,230
Don’t you want to try?

506
00:38:20,100 --> 00:38:21,740
Try what, you idiot?

507
00:38:22,640 --> 00:38:23,880
You said it—three months.

508
00:38:24,400 --> 00:38:25,360
Yeah.

509
00:38:34,150 --> 00:38:36,300
Seriously though, thanks.

510
00:38:36,610 --> 00:38:37,856
For handling everything for me.

511
00:38:39,030 --> 00:38:40,120
That damn case—

512
00:38:40,400 --> 00:38:41,190
it was a mess.

513
00:38:42,730 --> 00:38:43,380
So?

514
00:38:44,190 --> 00:38:45,200
What did O-lin say?

515
00:38:46,480 --> 00:38:47,000
Damn.

516
00:38:47,560 --> 00:38:49,720
She cried her eyes out.

517
00:38:50,200 --> 00:38:53,560
Told me she hasn’t slept since she caused Do’s death.

518
00:38:53,979 --> 00:38:55,790
She wants to confess to what she did.

519
00:38:56,360 --> 00:38:57,160
Damn it.

520
00:38:57,720 --> 00:39:00,630
Took her months to come to her senses.

521
00:39:01,330 --> 00:39:04,530
Look at me—covered in scars, almost the queen of the prison.

522
00:39:05,320 --> 00:39:06,160
Good thing

523
00:39:06,660 --> 00:39:09,160
my face isn’t ruined. Still gorgeous.

524
00:39:11,370 --> 00:39:12,130
Damn it.

525
00:39:13,740 --> 00:39:14,330
Hey.

526
00:39:14,930 --> 00:39:15,900
Where are you dropping me off?

527
00:39:16,360 --> 00:39:17,330
I’ve got class.

528
00:39:21,280 --> 00:39:22,990
Is our old condo floor still empty?

529
00:39:25,120 --> 00:39:25,950
Seriously?

530
00:39:26,410 --> 00:39:28,060
Of course it’s empty. The whole floor is.

531
00:39:28,720 --> 00:39:29,880
Who the hell would dare stay there?

532
00:39:30,270 --> 00:39:30,910
Yeah.

533
00:39:31,850 --> 00:39:33,170
Then drop me at the condo.

534
00:39:33,430 --> 00:39:33,970
Okay.

535
00:39:41,420 --> 00:39:44,370
Didn’t you tell me you were going to investigate some major national case?

536
00:39:44,570 --> 00:39:45,650
So what did you get?

537
00:39:45,800 --> 00:39:47,180
The case is closed, Papa.

538
00:39:48,290 --> 00:39:52,260
It ended so simply. I thought it’d be some huge case,

539
00:39:52,670 --> 00:39:55,440
involving some underground secret organization or something.

540
00:39:56,240 --> 00:39:57,230
Turns out,

541
00:39:58,030 --> 00:39:59,240
it was that simple.

542
00:40:01,830 --> 00:40:04,400
You even left a message asking us to take care of Khun John.

543
00:40:04,900 --> 00:40:07,220
Me and Daddy were so shocked.

544
00:40:08,470 --> 00:40:09,540
I’m sorry.

545
00:40:10,380 --> 00:40:13,060
It’s okay. We’re just glad you’re safe. I was worried.

546
00:40:13,330 --> 00:40:15,480
I’ll bring Khun John to you this Friday.

547
00:40:16,920 --> 00:40:18,090
Alright, Papa.

548
00:40:18,460 --> 00:40:19,760
I’ll be waiting.

549
00:40:21,240 --> 00:40:22,170
See you.

550
00:40:23,640 --> 00:40:24,120
Yes.

551
00:40:35,540 --> 00:40:38,470
I’m sorry I just got murdered, that’s all.

552
00:40:39,950 --> 00:40:42,110
Sorry my case wasn’t exciting enough.

553
00:40:50,340 --> 00:40:51,340
I’m scared, Dao.

554
00:40:53,530 --> 00:40:53,960
Hm?

555
00:40:55,820 --> 00:40:57,280
I’m scared I’ll disappear.

556
00:41:01,320 --> 00:41:02,780
Even I’m already a ghost, after all.

557
00:41:05,740 --> 00:41:07,610
How can a ghost and a human be in love?

558
00:41:09,250 --> 00:41:09,770
Yeah.

559
00:41:13,370 --> 00:41:15,220
You could at least comfort me a little.

560
00:41:20,630 --> 00:41:22,420
Hey, Dao, someone’s coming.

561
00:41:23,440 --> 00:41:24,470
Someone’s coming, Dao.

562
00:41:26,040 --> 00:41:27,500
Someone’s coming.

563
00:41:28,710 --> 00:41:29,880
Someone’s coming.

564
00:41:48,060 --> 00:41:48,720
Hey.

565
00:41:51,600 --> 00:41:52,650
Is Do still here?

566
00:42:02,390 --> 00:42:03,370
He’s not here anymore.

567
00:42:04,670 --> 00:42:07,320
Has he been reborn?

568
00:42:31,230 --> 00:42:32,790
I know you’re still here.

569
00:42:36,730 --> 00:42:37,630
Show yourself.

570
00:42:43,420 --> 00:42:44,320
Hurry up.

571
00:42:47,440 --> 00:42:48,860
I miss you.

572
00:43:19,920 --> 00:43:20,670
I...

573
00:43:24,080 --> 00:43:25,220
I miss you too.

574
00:43:43,080 --> 00:43:44,600
I miss you.

575
00:43:57,930 --> 00:43:58,550
You—

576
00:43:59,120 --> 00:44:01,220
why did you leave me?

577
00:44:12,920 --> 00:44:13,570
As for me,

578
00:44:14,750 --> 00:44:16,840
I didn’t want to trouble Dao and make him move out,

579
00:44:18,490 --> 00:44:21,020
so I rented the room across instead.

580
00:44:23,620 --> 00:44:24,310
So?

581
00:44:26,800 --> 00:44:27,730
Pretty cool, right?

582
00:44:33,140 --> 00:44:34,280
That way we can stay close.

583
00:44:37,360 --> 00:44:38,590
On the way here, I—

584
00:44:38,800 --> 00:44:41,420
had Arthit stop to buy pad kra pao from the place we used to eat.

585
00:44:43,130 --> 00:44:46,260
It’s not as good as Aunt Joom’s, your favorite, though.

586
00:44:58,890 --> 00:44:59,740
But just eat it anyway.

587
00:45:11,410 --> 00:45:12,120
You know,

588
00:45:16,080 --> 00:45:17,720
I’ve never wanted to see ghosts.

589
00:45:26,400 --> 00:45:27,110
But today,

590
00:45:33,540 --> 00:45:34,930
I really wish I could see you.

591
00:46:00,450 --> 00:46:02,121
What’s up, Grandma’s boy?

592
00:46:03,670 --> 00:46:05,090
Hello, Khun Phuangthong.

593
00:46:06,680 --> 00:46:08,660
Is there a way for a normal person

594
00:46:08,970 --> 00:46:11,040
to talk to a spirit?

595
00:46:11,757 --> 00:46:15,117
Why would you want to? It goes against nature.

596
00:46:17,070 --> 00:46:19,450
I’ve talked to him many times already, Khun Phuangthong.

597
00:46:19,860 --> 00:46:21,430
We’re practically close now.

598
00:46:23,520 --> 00:46:25,970
There is a way, though.

599
00:46:33,410 --> 00:46:34,970
Will it really work, Dao?

600
00:46:37,760 --> 00:46:39,650
I’m not sure either.

601
00:46:56,730 --> 00:46:59,411
You have to wear a dead person’s shirt and hold your breath.

602
00:46:59,453 --> 00:47:01,920
Then you’ll see the spirit of the shirt’s owner.

603
00:47:37,180 --> 00:47:38,230
You bastard.

604
00:47:41,760 --> 00:47:43,310
You still look stupid as ever.

605
00:47:45,140 --> 00:47:46,640
Yeah, like you’re any prettier.

606
00:47:51,330 --> 00:47:52,290
How’ve you been?

607
00:47:53,160 --> 00:47:55,530
What about you? You doing okay?

608
00:47:59,980 --> 00:48:01,210
I’m good.

609
00:48:14,750 --> 00:48:16,300
Michael still misses her.

610
00:48:19,520 --> 00:48:22,860
Even if we’re touched by P'Meen and P'Do’s love,

611
00:48:23,460 --> 00:48:25,010
I won’t go back to missing him.

612
00:48:25,690 --> 00:48:26,540
Really?

613
00:48:29,150 --> 00:48:29,750
Mm.

614
00:48:31,590 --> 00:48:32,380
Really.

615
00:48:33,250 --> 00:48:34,730
Does it still hurt, Michael?

616
00:48:38,040 --> 00:48:38,880
Not anymore.

617
00:48:39,850 --> 00:48:42,890
Even though he just texted you, you don’t feel anything?

618
00:48:57,500 --> 00:48:59,306
I’ll be back in Thailand in two months.

619
00:48:59,622 --> 00:49:00,327
Don’t block me.

620
00:49:00,628 --> 00:49:02,208
Even if you do, I’ll just make a new account.

621
00:49:34,010 --> 00:49:35,010
How much for a cigarette?

622
00:49:38,800 --> 00:49:39,670
A hundred each.

623
00:49:42,020 --> 00:49:44,020
Put it on my tab. My cash is in the room.

624
00:49:47,050 --> 00:49:47,770
Fine.

625
00:50:13,910 --> 00:50:14,870
Nice lighter.

626
00:50:18,810 --> 00:50:19,450
How much?

627
00:50:23,000 --> 00:50:24,830
Are you seriously going to buy everything?

628
00:50:27,740 --> 00:50:28,600
Yeah.

629
00:50:29,370 --> 00:50:30,240
How much?

630
00:50:31,570 --> 00:50:32,630
Two thousand.

631
00:50:49,730 --> 00:50:51,170
Didn’t you say you quit smoking?

632
00:50:59,050 --> 00:50:59,910
Sorry.

633
00:51:00,720 --> 00:51:03,090
You always like this whenever you miss him.

634
00:51:04,150 --> 00:51:04,970
No.

635
00:51:05,350 --> 00:51:06,660
I don’t miss him.

636
00:51:13,630 --> 00:51:15,470
Emma, stop nagging.

637
00:51:19,490 --> 00:51:21,690
Since when did you become such a nag?

638
00:51:22,550 --> 00:51:24,290
I’m not talking to you anymore.

639
00:51:47,420 --> 00:51:48,240
What is it?

640
00:51:49,010 --> 00:51:49,810
Direk.

641
00:51:52,180 --> 00:51:53,000
Direk.

642
00:51:53,260 --> 00:51:55,390
What’s wrong? Why are you freaking out?

643
00:51:58,690 --> 00:51:59,420
Direk.

644
00:52:00,090 --> 00:52:01,390
It’s Emma, Direk.

645
00:52:02,420 --> 00:52:04,630
I heard that kid next door who can talk to ghosts.

646
00:52:06,650 --> 00:52:08,520
I heard him talking to Emma, Direk.

647
00:52:11,260 --> 00:52:12,920
I heard him call Emma’s name.

648
00:52:13,310 --> 00:52:15,190
What are you talking about? This isn’t funny.

649
00:52:19,060 --> 00:52:20,430
Emma’s still here, Direk.

650
00:52:26,210 --> 00:52:27,190
Mom’s still here, Direk.

651
00:52:31,040 --> 00:52:32,200
Mom’s still here.

652
00:52:47,268 --> 00:52:49,044
That kid can talk to ghosts.

653
00:52:49,890 --> 00:52:52,157
He can see them and communicate with spirits.

654
00:52:52,715 --> 00:52:54,845
Are you thinking of asking him to help find Emma?

655
00:52:56,140 --> 00:52:58,386
Hey, North. Can I get your friend’s Line ID?

656
00:52:58,451 --> 00:53:00,176
Are you trying to hit on my friend?

657
00:53:01,508 --> 00:53:02,192
Hey.

658
00:53:02,795 --> 00:53:04,139
You’ve already helped me,

659
00:53:04,502 --> 00:53:05,943
can you help me a little more?

660
00:53:07,475 --> 00:53:08,888
What made you dye your hair that color?

